====Usage notes====
*Although well attested, this term is often claimed to be non-standard and can make the speaker or writer sound ignorant. To avoid this controversey, the use of “regardless” or other synonym is advocated in its place.

====Synonyms====
*(''regardless''): [[irrespective]], [[regardless]]

===References===
*Webster’s New International Dictionary (1909) labels '''irregardless''' as an ‘erroneous or humerous form’.
*The Shorter OED labels '''irregardless''' as ‘chiefly ''N. Amer.'' (''non-standard'' or ''joc.'')’.
*This term is notably omitted from the Etymological Dictionary of the English Language (1910), Fowler's Modern English Usage (1965){{,}} and Roget’s 21st Century Thesaurus (1992)

